<h1><i class="fa fa-link"></i>Adding Attachments</h1>

<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#help"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>Help</a></li>
	<li><a href="#help/sharing-messages"><i class="fa fa-comment"></i>Sharing Messages</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-link"></i>Adding Attachments</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p>When sending direct messages, comments, and replies, you can attach pictures, files and folders. </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-image"></i>Adding Pictures</h2>
			<p>To add one or more pictures to your message, click on the "Add Pictures" button underneath the message box. This will bring up a selector dialog where you can choose pictures to add. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/add-images-button.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Add Pictures Button</div>
			</div>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/adding-images.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Adding Pictures</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-th"></i>Image Galleries</h2>
			<p>If you add more than one image to a message, then they will be arranged in an image gallery. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/message-with-gallery.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Message with an Image Gallery</div>
			</div>

			<p>If you add more than 6 images to a message, then the first 6 will be arranged in an image gallery and a button will be appended in the lower right corner to access the others (see figure below). </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/message-with-large-gallery.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Message with a 10 Image Gallery</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-file"></i>Adding Files</h2>
			<p>You can also add any type of file to your message including music, documents and data files. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/add-files-button.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Add Files Button</div>
			</div>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/adding-files.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Adding Files</div>
			</div>

			<p>Below we see a message with a file attachment.  Viewers can open and view or listen to the file by double-clicking the file icon. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/message-with-file.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Message with a File Attachment</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-folder"></i>Adding Folders</h2>
			<p>You can also add entire folders to your message.  Double-clicking the folder icon will open up the <a href="#apps/file-browser">File Browser</a> enabling users to navigate and open files contained in this folder. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/message-with-folder.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Message with a Folder Attachment</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-upload"></i>Uploading Files</h2>
			<p>You can also add files to messages from your local file system.  Clicking this button will allow you to select your local files and then will upload them and attach them to your new message in a single step. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img src="images/help/sharing-messages/adding-attachments/upload-file-button.png" />
				<div class="caption">Upload File Button</div>
			</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>